results.description:
Observed this unique snake specimen for a good 10min on a hilltop overlooking Larung Gar buddhist college, Sertar county (色达 Seda in Chinese), Garze （甘孜 Ganzi), Sichuan province, China.
Sunny afternoon, altitude 4000-4100m. 
Location indicated on Google Earth map should be correct, but if wrong then it is within 50-100m to the SW (going up the hill).
The snake could be approached easily and photographed, though it raised its head in a viper-like way at some point.

comments.body:
@jingyin666 You mean the newly described species *Gloydius rubromaculatus*?

For anyone who wants to check, it seems to be this paper describing it (Red-spotted alpine pit viper or Tongtianhe pit viper): https://brill.com/view/journals/amre/38/4/article-p517_10.xml
@jingyin666 Feel free to suggest this ID
